This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and information credibility evaluation. It also involves deep learning approaches and adversarial networks, which are commonly used in the field of NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning models and strategies for feature extraction and classification. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with evaluating the credibility of information on the internet. 

Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as detecting fake news is a crucial aspect of ensuring the security and integrity of information on the internet.
